- Good luck.
- Bye.

234
00:20:53,711 --> 00:20:57,214
<i>If I go there will be trouble</i>

235
00:20:57,339 --> 00:20:59,008
Why did you do that?

236
00:20:59,133 --> 00:21:01,677
- What?
- All that, in front of me.

237
00:21:02,845 --> 00:21:06,098
You know what I should do?
Arrange to have his cover withdrawn...

238
00:21:06,182 --> 00:21:08,809
and I should put him al fuera and you, too.

239
00:21:08,893 --> 00:21:11,854
But you're not going to, though. Are you?

240
00:21:13,355 --> 00:21:15,733
Why are you being so nice to me?

241
00:21:16,233 --> 00:21:18,194
Are you hoping for a reward?

242
00:21:18,861 --> 00:21:21,030
How do you get the papeles out?

243
00:21:26,702 --> 00:21:29,997
At the beginning of every new batch
we do a test run.

244
00:21:30,122 --> 00:21:31,624
Then we destroy the papel.

245
00:21:31,707 --> 00:21:34,835
I go in to work
and I have a fake papel under my tongue.

246
00:21:34,919 --> 00:21:38,756
I destroy the fake one
and put the real papel under my tongue.

247
00:21:38,964 --> 00:21:43,344
I then go to the bathroom,
put the papel into a pill, swallow it.

248
00:21:43,552 --> 00:21:47,389
A couple of days later, I have the papel.

249
00:21:48,724 --> 00:21:50,267
Impressed?

250
00:21:51,227 --> 00:21:53,062
Come on, be impressed.

251
00:23:44,131 --> 00:23:48,052
Thank you for bringing me home.
It's very kind of you.

252
00:24:08,238 --> 00:24:09,448
Come in.

253
00:24:20,501 --> 00:24:23,170
Beautiful. You have green fingers.

254
00:24:25,381 --> 00:24:28,133
Everything is controlled scientifically.

255
00:24:30,010 --> 00:24:32,971
Do you think that sunlight
is as dangerous as they say?

256
00:24:33,722 --> 00:24:34,848
I hope not.

257
00:24:36,225 --> 00:24:40,020
- Would you like a drink? A glass of water?
- Sure.

258
00:24:40,729 --> 00:24:44,149
One of my fingers
is younger than the others.

259
00:24:44,233 --> 00:24:46,068
- Really?
- Yeah.

260
00:24:46,193 --> 00:24:49,113
- Which one?
- This one.

261
00:24:51,198 --> 00:24:52,658
Do you like it?

262
00:24:54,410 --> 00:24:55,786
Very much.

263
00:24:56,412 --> 00:24:59,540
It's much better than the other fingers.
Definitely.

264
00:25:00,082 --> 00:25:03,419
Maybe I should get them
to grow me a younger face.

265
00:25:05,963 --> 00:25:07,047
No.

266
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:11,218
I love the sorrows of your changing face.

267
00:25:12,177 --> 00:25:13,679
Or whatever it is.

268
00:25:24,481 --> 00:25:27,067
I haven't seen this book in a while.

269
00:25:28,152 --> 00:25:30,904
"In a friend one should have
one's best enemy...

270
00:25:31,864 --> 00:25:35,576
"and you should be closest to him
when you resist him."

271
00:26:04,980 --> 00:26:06,106
Look.

272
00:26:09,777 --> 00:26:12,154
It's all I've got left from my childhood.

273
00:26:12,988 --> 00:26:14,990
I keep my special memories here.

274
00:26:16,825 --> 00:26:19,745
- Who are they?
- My father and mother.

275
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:21,830
Before we left Shanghai.

276
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:28,629
These are people like Damian,
when I give them the papeles.

277
00:26:31,340 --> 00:26:33,425
Now you know all my secrets.

278
00:26:36,762 --> 00:26:39,014
I love to look at their faces.

279
00:26:40,557 --> 00:26:42,392
They're so beautiful.

280
00:26:43,477 --> 00:26:45,229
Look at their eyes.

281
00:26:46,522 --> 00:26:49,233
They have a look
that the rest of us don't have.

282
00:26:52,820 --> 00:26:54,780
You look like them un poco.

283
00:27:04,581 --> 00:27:06,458
You should go to sleep.

284
00:27:19,221 --> 00:27:22,766
I don't want to go to sleep.
Please don't let me sleep.

285
00:27:31,733 --> 00:27:33,402
I'll make you some coffee.

286
00:29:09,206 --> 00:29:10,415
Coffee.

287
00:29:37,234 --> 00:29:39,236
<i>Said I remember</i>

288
00:29:40,529 --> 00:29:42,698
<i>When we used to sit</i>

289
00:29:43,657 --> 00:29:48,161
<i>In a government yard in Trenchtown</i>

290
00:29:48,370 --> 00:29:53,041
<i>And Georgie would make the firelight</i>

291
00:29:53,583 --> 00:29:57,796
<i>Logwood burning through the night</i>

292
00:29:58,380 --> 00:30:01,800
<i>No woman, no cry</i>

293
00:30:03,176 --> 00:30:06,638
<i>No woman, no cry</i>

294
00:30:07,097 --> 00:30:10,600
I was just gonna torture the song
and now you're murdering it.

295
00:30:10,726 --> 00:30:12,060
I'm tone-deaf.

296
00:30:13,603 --> 00:30:15,355
You find that attractive?

297
00:32:38,039 --> 00:32:39,457
Are you leaving?

298
00:32:41,042 --> 00:32:43,003
I'm booked on a flight home.

299
00:32:44,171 --> 00:32:47,340
- What time's your flight?
- 11:00.

300
00:32:48,049 --> 00:32:50,093
What will happen to Bikku?

301
00:32:52,804 --> 00:32:54,639
He'll lose his cover.

302
00:32:56,391 --> 00:32:57,893
That's bad.

303
00:32:58,268 --> 00:33:00,187
I know it's bad.

304
00:33:00,270 --> 00:33:04,024
You giving out fake papers is bad.
Me letting you off is bad.

305
00:33:04,149 --> 00:33:06,776
Have you ever lived outside?

306
00:33:11,239 --> 00:33:13,033
I was outside for 10 years.

307
00:33:22,584 --> 00:33:23,919
<i>Lo siento.</i>

308
00:33:48,443 --> 00:33:49,861
I have to go.

309
00:34:32,445 --> 00:34:35,740
- I need to stop at the entry checkpoint.
- Why?

310
00:34:36,574 --> 00:34:39,160
I need to get more sherbet fountains.

311
00:35:09,065 --> 00:35:10,442
Hi, mister.

312
00:35:12,027 --> 00:35:15,280
I found this.
I thought you could put it to good use.

313
00:35:15,363 --> 00:35:18,158
Thank you. Gracias. God bless you. Go.

314
00:35:19,951 --> 00:35:21,119
Sorry.

315
00:35:22,579 --> 00:35:25,415
Leave him alone.
Thank you, God bless you.

316
00:35:27,876 --> 00:35:29,878
<i>If we had enough information...</i>

317
00:35:30,003 --> 00:35:32,839
<i>we could predict
the consequences of our actions.</i>

318
00:35:34,257 --> 00:35:36,134
<i>Would you want to know?</i>

319
00:35:36,509 --> 00:35:39,512
<i>If you kiss that girl,
if you talk to that man...</i>

320
00:35:39,638 --> 00:35:43,516
<i>if you take that job or marry that woman
or steal that papel?</i>

321
00:35:43,850 --> 00:35:46,019
<i>If we knew what would happen in the end...</i>

322
00:35:46,102 --> 00:35:49,898
<i>would we ever be able to take the
first step, to make the first move?</i>

323
00:35:56,821 --> 00:35:58,615
Hello, I'm home.

324
00:36:06,873 --> 00:36:10,168
- Did you have a good trip?
- It went all right.

325
00:36:14,297 --> 00:36:17,300
Daddy! Where have you been?

326
00:36:17,425 --> 00:36:21,179
<i>They'd be pleased to see you.
Your wife, your special boy.</i>

327
00:36:22,263 --> 00:36:24,391
<i>They'd want to know all your news...</i>

328
00:36:24,516 --> 00:36:27,519
<i>and will be glad to have you home,
safe and sound.</i>

329
00:36:30,772 --> 00:36:33,024
- Want me to guess what you're thinking?
- Yeah.

330
00:36:37,696 --> 00:36:39,864
<i>- Bicycle.
- Si.</i>

331
00:36:46,162 --> 00:36:49,040
<i>I can't answer right now,
so leave a message.</i>

332
00:36:50,208 --> 00:36:53,586
It's William, call me.
Just to let me know you're okay.

333
00:36:55,088 --> 00:36:56,172
Bye.

334
00:37:11,104 --> 00:37:13,231
- Are you tired?
- Yeah.

335
00:37:16,901 --> 00:37:18,778
<i>Did you think about me at all?</i>

336
00:37:20,488 --> 00:37:23,324
<i>Did you try to imagine
what was happening to me?</i>

337
00:37:23,908 --> 00:37:26,745
<i>Does an empathy virus work long-distance?</i>

338
00:37:59,819 --> 00:38:04,282
<i>Maria Gonzalez, age 25.
Employee of the Sphinx.</i>

339
00:38:05,617 --> 00:38:08,119
<i>Nurture father: Christian Gunter.</i>

340
00:38:08,578 --> 00:38:12,832
<i>Born in Freeport of Jebel Ali.
Transferred to Shanghai.</i>

341
00:38:13,082 --> 00:38:15,960
<i>He was exiled for financial irregularities.</i>

342
00:38:16,211 --> 00:38:19,297
<i>Recorded in Kunming, Dhanbad...</i>

343
00:38:19,380 --> 00:38:21,841
<i>Quetta and Baghdad.</i>

344
00:38:22,091 --> 00:38:25,595
<i>Presumed to be returning
to the Freeport of Jebel Ali.</i>

345
00:38:27,222 --> 00:38:29,849
<i>Carmen Gonzalez returned to Shanghai.</i>

346
00:38:32,227 --> 00:38:33,728
<i>Remarried to-</i>

347
00:38:35,396 --> 00:38:36,940
<i>Maria Gonzalez.</i>

348
00:38:37,398 --> 00:38:40,276
<i>Height: 165 cms.</i>

349
00:38:40,568 --> 00:38:43,196
Buenos dias. De Souza wants to talk to you.

350
00:38:43,279 --> 00:38:45,865
- What about?
- There's been a fatality in Asia.

351
00:38:45,949 --> 00:38:48,451
A guy was traveling on one of the papers
from Shanghai.

352
00:38:48,868 --> 00:38:52,247
- She's waiting. You want a coffee?
- No, thanks.

353
00:38:53,331 --> 00:38:56,376
<i>- Hello.
- Someone died yesterday.</i>

354
00:38:56,918 --> 00:38:58,920
I heard. Do you have details?

355
00:38:59,295 --> 00:39:02,757
<i>Hombre had una cosa about bats,
wanted to go to Delhi.</i>

356
00:39:02,841 --> 00:39:05,802
<i>The place to be if you like bats, apparently.</i>

357
00:39:06,511 --> 00:39:11,349
<i>Couldn't get cover because he had an
ineluctable disposition to Ward's Disease.</i>

358
00:39:12,600 --> 00:39:14,143
<i>Do you know it?</i>

359
00:39:14,352 --> 00:39:16,145
<i>- No.
- It makes you bleed to death.</i>

360
00:39:16,271 --> 00:39:18,398
<i>Most people in Delhi are immune,
which is why...</i>

361
00:39:18,481 --> 00:39:22,569
this hombre couldn't get cover,
which is why he bought fake papeles...

362
00:39:22,986 --> 00:39:25,280
<i>which is why he bled to death yesterday.</i>

363
00:39:25,405 --> 00:39:29,576
<i>- What was his name?
- Alekan. Damian Alekan.</i>

364
00:39:31,327 --> 00:39:35,832
<i>The papeles come from the same printer
as the ones you investigated.</i>

365
00:39:38,585 --> 00:39:39,878
I'm sorry.

366
00:39:40,211 --> 00:39:43,339
<i>Get back, make it right,
then you won't have to be sorry anymore.</i>

367
00:39:43,464 --> 00:39:47,135
<i>- Is there someone else you can send?
- Why would you want me to do that?</i>

368
00:39:47,969 --> 00:39:52,432
I had some trouble when I was there.
Some trouble with the virus, I think.

369
00:39:53,808 --> 00:39:56,102
<i>We all have problems, William.</i>

370
00:39:56,477 --> 00:39:59,522
<i>How we deal with them
is a measure of our worth.</i>

371
00:39:59,647 --> 00:40:01,107
<i>Go back tomorrow.</i>

372
00:40:05,653 --> 00:40:07,280
Damian Alekan.

373
00:40:28,384 --> 00:40:32,013
- Where did you get that? Someone gave it-
- I have to go back to Shanghai.

374
00:40:32,138 --> 00:40:34,140
How long will you be away?

375
00:40:34,265 --> 00:40:36,267
I have a 24-hour cover.

376
00:40:36,684 --> 00:40:38,853
I'll be back before you know I've gone.

377
00:40:39,103 --> 00:40:40,813
Messed it all up.

378
00:41:50,091 --> 00:41:51,300
Welcome, sir.

379
00:42:04,564 --> 00:42:07,025
Three more forged papeles reported.

380
00:42:07,191 --> 00:42:09,902
One here, one in Sao Paolo, one in Delhi.

381
00:42:10,862 --> 00:42:13,322
If this doesn't stop,
I could lose my own cover.

382
00:42:13,448 --> 00:42:16,868
Lo siento, it's the first time
my intuition has let me down.

383
00:42:16,951 --> 00:42:20,079
I think he had an accomplice.
There was a woman here last time...

384
00:42:20,204 --> 00:42:22,331
- Maria Gonzalez.
- She's gone.

385
00:42:24,167 --> 00:42:26,586
What do you mean gone? Disappeared?

386
00:42:26,836 --> 00:42:28,880
I was told she had a body issue.

387
00:42:29,464 --> 00:42:31,090
It was all official.

388
00:42:49,067 --> 00:42:50,276
Maria?

389
00:42:51,944 --> 00:42:53,905
Video Listo Corporation.

390
00:42:54,614 --> 00:42:58,451
Hello. I just tried to get in my apartment
and the video listo no funciona.

391
00:42:58,534 --> 00:43:02,038
<i>We have your number listed
as temporarily descontinuado.</i>

392
00:43:02,163 --> 00:43:04,624
Do I look descontinuado to you?

393
00:43:04,874 --> 00:43:07,627
<i>No, senor, but then I don't know
that you're the holder.</i>

394
00:43:07,710 --> 00:43:11,005
- That's not my problem, is it?
- If you can give me your palabra...

395
00:43:11,130 --> 00:43:14,467
<i>I can provide you with a 10-minute window
to recode your video listo.</i>

396
00:43:14,550 --> 00:43:17,303
<i>- How would that be?
- That would be great, thank you.</i>

397
00:43:17,428 --> 00:43:19,347
- Palabra, sir?
- Panoply.

398
00:43:27,355 --> 00:43:29,899
<i>Did you know what you were looking for?</i>

399
00:43:30,024 --> 00:43:32,485
<i>Or were you hoping I had left you a clue?</i>

400
00:43:32,610 --> 00:43:36,322
<i>Like Hansel and Gretel
being dragged off into the woods.</i>

401
00:43:39,575 --> 00:43:40,660
Panoply.

402
00:43:46,082 --> 00:43:48,793
<i>Maria, today you have no appointments.</i>

403
00:43:54,757 --> 00:43:59,303
<i>Maria, today you have a 3:15 appointment
at the Mai Lin Clinic.</i>

404
00:44:10,356 --> 00:44:14,193
I'm investigating a fraud
to which Maria Gonzalez is a key witness.

405
00:44:14,652 --> 00:44:17,780
I was officially informed
that she has some body issues...

406
00:44:17,905 --> 00:44:19,240
and was on a happiness break.

407
00:44:19,740 --> 00:44:21,951
She has been relocated.

408
00:44:22,118 --> 00:44:25,538
There were complications
that we couldn't deal with.

409
00:44:25,621 --> 00:44:27,415
She has been sent outside.

410
00:44:27,665 --> 00:44:31,752
Outside is a big place,
it would help if you were more specific.

411
00:44:32,295 --> 00:44:35,756
There's a confidentiality issue there,
I'm afraid, sir.

412
00:44:36,632 --> 00:44:38,593
What was the nature of her body issue?

413
00:44:38,885 --> 00:44:42,054
There's a confidentiality issue there,
I'm afraid, sir.

414
00:44:42,471 --> 00:44:44,849
Why was she summoned
for a happiness break?

415
00:44:45,766 --> 00:44:48,102
Is this a training exercise?

416
00:44:48,769 --> 00:44:52,190
- Are you trying to catch me out?
- You got me.

417
00:44:52,273 --> 00:44:55,693
- You didn't get me, though.
- You are top of the class.

418
00:44:57,445 --> 00:45:02,033
Very good.
Tell me something about yourself, anything.

419
00:45:02,158 --> 00:45:03,993
For the report. I have to write this up.

420
00:45:05,953 --> 00:45:08,998
My mother had this job before me.

421
00:45:09,498 --> 00:45:11,125
I inherited it.

422
00:45:14,545 --> 00:45:16,923
How long has Miss Gonzalez
been pregnant?

423
00:45:18,633 --> 00:45:20,009
I never said that.

424
00:45:20,968 --> 00:45:23,679
What type of Code 46 violation was it?

425
00:45:25,306 --> 00:45:27,433
I never mentioned Code 46.

426
00:45:30,144 --> 00:45:32,271
Where is the Mai Lin Clinic?

427
00:45:32,855 --> 00:45:36,442
There's a confidentiality issue there,
I'm afraid, sir.

428
00:45:37,860 --> 00:45:39,403
Thank you for your help.

429
00:45:50,498 --> 00:45:53,876
You rented a car. The clinic was al fuera.

430
00:45:54,293 --> 00:45:56,629
170 K outside the city.

431
00:46:05,179 --> 00:46:07,848
<i>I imagine you like a medieval knight
on a quest.</i>

432
00:46:09,350 --> 00:46:10,518
<i>A quest for me.</i>

433
00:46:30,705 --> 00:46:32,498
I'm here to see Maria Gonzalez.

434
00:46:32,623 --> 00:46:35,167
<i>Lo siento,
no visitors are permitted until 6:00.</i>

435
00:46:35,293 --> 00:46:39,255
I'm from Westerfields.
She's a key witness in a major fraud case.

436
00:46:39,630 --> 00:46:41,966
<i>- Nombre?
- Maria Gonzalez.</i>

437
00:46:42,258 --> 00:46:45,636
<i>- Tu nombre?
- William Geld. I'm with Westerfields.</i>

438
00:46:45,720 --> 00:46:47,013
I need your print here.

439
00:46:47,138 --> 00:46:49,265
It's a very urgent situation.

440
00:46:49,682 --> 00:46:51,642
I know. Nombre and print.

441
00:46:53,310 --> 00:46:57,898
I can tell by looking at you
that you are not just...

442
00:46:58,774 --> 00:47:00,443
a keypad presser.

443
00:47:00,693 --> 00:47:02,028
You can make judgments.

444
00:47:02,111 --> 00:47:04,864
Si, and I have made my
judgment about you.

445
00:47:04,947 --> 00:47:08,075
If you don't have authorization
for this place...

446
00:47:09,076 --> 00:47:11,704
Tell me one thing about yourself.
Anything at all.

447
00:47:11,787 --> 00:47:12,788
Okay.

448
00:47:13,456 --> 00:47:14,874
I'm tired.

449
00:47:14,957 --> 00:47:18,169
I have conversations like this one a lot.
Is that enough?

450
00:47:18,252 --> 00:47:22,798
If I were able to guess your palabra,
would you be impressed?

451
00:47:22,923 --> 00:47:24,759
I would be dumbfounded.

452
00:47:25,092 --> 00:47:28,679
- It's "Garamond."
- No, it's not. It's nothing like that.

453
00:47:29,597 --> 00:47:32,683
Did you have an empathy virus?
