prior to your arriving here.

492
00:50:15,846 --> 00:50:18,265
I'm tired. I would like to rest.

493
00:50:20,309 --> 00:50:22,811
Miss Gonzalez is still in recovery.

494
00:50:35,115 --> 00:50:36,200
Why is she in here?

495
00:50:36,283 --> 00:50:39,536
And, please, do not use the word "finger"
at any point in your answer.

496
00:50:39,620 --> 00:50:42,164
- Her finger-
- Was damaged and regrown...

497
00:50:42,289 --> 00:50:45,167
on her family's insurance policy
22 years ago.

498
00:50:45,292 --> 00:50:47,127
I know a great deal about Miss Gonzalez.

499
00:50:47,253 --> 00:50:50,214
For instance, that she was pregnant
when she came in here.

500
00:50:50,339 --> 00:50:52,633
I also know,
because you told me so yourself...

501
00:50:52,758 --> 00:50:55,844
that you have no interest
in impeding my investigation.

502
00:50:57,429 --> 00:50:59,556
She violated Code 46.

503
00:51:00,933 --> 00:51:02,393
We've terminated the pregnancy...

504
00:51:02,518 --> 00:51:05,354
and taken out the memory cluster
immediately around it.

505
00:51:06,313 --> 00:51:08,315
- The baby was terminated?
- There was no baby.

506
00:51:08,440 --> 00:51:12,152
Just a pregnancy which is now terminated
and the memories removed.

507
00:51:16,824 --> 00:51:19,285
You've interfered...

508
00:51:20,953 --> 00:51:23,789
with the memory of a key witness
in an insurance fraud.

509
00:51:23,914 --> 00:51:25,291
The memories were very local.

510
00:51:25,416 --> 00:51:28,377
It's just the man, the sex act,
and the pregnancy.

511
00:51:29,253 --> 00:51:31,297
She doesn't remember the man at all?

512
00:51:31,422 --> 00:51:34,174
The man, the sex, the pregnancy.
We've erased all of them.

513
00:51:34,300 --> 00:51:37,011
Apart from that,
it's the same Maria Gonzalez.

514
00:51:37,428 --> 00:51:40,639
The finger is a placebo memory.
I moved it from her childhood.

515
00:51:40,723 --> 00:51:42,558
I think it's very effective.

516
00:51:45,352 --> 00:51:47,646
When will she be able to leave?

517
00:51:48,272 --> 00:51:49,732
She's due to leave tomorrow.

518
00:51:49,857 --> 00:51:53,652
I'm afraid I'm gonna have to ask you
to release her to me now.

519
00:51:58,032 --> 00:52:00,492
<i>Can you miss someone
you don't remember?</i>

520
00:52:00,618 --> 00:52:04,038
<i>Can one moment or experience
ever disappear completely?</i>

521
00:52:04,872 --> 00:52:08,876
<i>Or does it always exist somewhere,
waiting to be discovered?</i>

522
00:52:10,586 --> 00:52:12,838
- Wait, I've forgotten something.
- What?

523
00:52:13,130 --> 00:52:17,009
- A valise. It's very important to me.
- It's in the back. Voila.

524
00:52:29,480 --> 00:52:31,440
Is that what you're going to do?

525
00:52:32,274 --> 00:52:34,318
Put me al fuera with them?

526
00:52:36,695 --> 00:52:40,032
You've been outside before.
Spent 10 years al fuera.

527
00:52:40,616 --> 00:52:42,826
Didn't come back inside till you were 14.

528
00:52:43,035 --> 00:52:44,703
You really did your homework.

529
00:52:45,621 --> 00:52:50,250
You can't sing, you like sherbet fountains,
you like to grow real plants from seed.

530
00:52:51,585 --> 00:52:54,213
God, I must have been
your favorite subject at school.

531
00:52:54,421 --> 00:52:56,173
You hate the desert.

532
00:52:59,718 --> 00:53:01,679
<i>I always hated the desert.</i>

533
00:53:02,971 --> 00:53:05,808
<i>Even at college,
studying the Roadrunner cartoons...</i>

534
00:53:05,933 --> 00:53:07,434
<i>I had to look away.</i>

535
00:53:09,269 --> 00:53:13,399
I've always wondered why the coyote
didn't just go out and buy a roadrunner.

536
00:53:13,607 --> 00:53:16,235
If he had enough money
for rocket-powered roller skates...

537
00:53:16,360 --> 00:53:18,779
he had enough money to buy a roadrunner.

538
00:53:20,781 --> 00:53:22,491
How did you do that?

539
00:53:24,159 --> 00:53:25,202
What?

540
00:53:25,994 --> 00:53:30,165
I was thinking something and
you heard me. That is weird.

541
00:53:31,375 --> 00:53:32,668
Intuition.

542
00:53:33,085 --> 00:53:36,422
I can feel what you're thinking.

543
00:53:36,547 --> 00:53:40,426
I don't believe in mind-reading.
I think it is all a trick.

544
00:53:40,676 --> 00:53:42,719
It's not a trick. It is a gift.

545
00:53:44,346 --> 00:53:46,223
What am I thinking now?

546
00:53:52,146 --> 00:53:54,940
You're thinking of Damian Alekan.

547
00:54:09,496 --> 00:54:12,499
- Have you been here before?
- Once.

548
00:54:14,626 --> 00:54:15,961
You like it?

549
00:54:16,503 --> 00:54:18,172
I was only here a day.

550
00:54:20,674 --> 00:54:23,427
But, yes, I liked it very much.

551
00:54:55,042 --> 00:54:56,710
Excuse the mess.

552
00:55:09,681 --> 00:55:10,974
Come here.

553
00:55:20,526 --> 00:55:21,735
Sit down.

554
00:55:37,417 --> 00:55:38,877
That's Damian.

555
00:55:41,588 --> 00:55:43,257
Recognize him now?

556
00:55:50,848 --> 00:55:53,058
I remember he wanted to go to Delhi.

557
00:55:54,017 --> 00:55:57,396
And I remember the look on his face
when I gave him the papel.

558
00:55:58,855 --> 00:56:02,442
He tried for years to get one officially
and he couldn't get one.

559
00:56:16,915 --> 00:56:21,712
I was there when you met Damian.
I was with you in the bar.

560
00:56:24,339 --> 00:56:25,674
I don't understand.

561
00:56:25,799 --> 00:56:28,927
You don't remember
because they erased your memory.

562
00:56:30,762 --> 00:56:33,056
I don't know what you're talking about.

563
00:56:35,267 --> 00:56:38,061
I came to Shanghai to investigate a fraud.

564
00:56:39,980 --> 00:56:41,899
I knew you were guilty.

565
00:56:44,276 --> 00:56:46,653
But then I fell in love with you.

566
00:56:54,536 --> 00:56:57,164
Why would they erase my memory of you?

567
00:57:00,459 --> 00:57:01,835
I don't know.

568
00:57:15,015 --> 00:57:16,975
My cosa. Where's my cosa?

569
00:57:23,607 --> 00:57:27,361
- I can't find my cosa.
- Come here. You haven't lost anything.

570
00:57:27,486 --> 00:57:28,528
Calm down.

571
00:57:28,654 --> 00:57:30,989
- I can't find my cosa.
- It's okay.

572
00:57:31,490 --> 00:57:33,742
I don't know where my cosa is.

573
00:57:37,955 --> 00:57:39,790
Will you stay with me?

574
00:57:46,129 --> 00:57:49,466
- I'm so tired.
- I'll stay with you until you wake up.

575
00:57:52,427 --> 00:57:54,846
- What is it?
- It'll help you sleep.

576
00:58:01,353 --> 00:58:05,023
- I don't understand anything.
- I don't understand anything either.

577
00:58:08,902 --> 00:58:12,155
<i>My father used to tell me stories
as I fell asleep.</i>

578
00:58:13,323 --> 00:58:16,201
<i>Stories about Jebel Ali and the Arabian Sea.</i>

579
00:58:19,371 --> 00:58:21,623
<i>Stories of magic and adventure.</i>

580
00:58:23,166 --> 00:58:24,668
<i>He used to live there...</i>

581
00:58:24,793 --> 00:58:28,922
<i>and believed that if we could return,
everything would be all right.</i>

582
00:58:30,173 --> 00:58:34,094
<i>Everything would be like it used to be
before we were exiled.</i>

583
00:58:39,266 --> 00:58:41,393
<i>And in my dreams I was there.</i>

584
00:58:53,947 --> 00:58:55,449
Sample, please.

585
00:58:56,366 --> 00:58:57,701
Thank you.

586
00:59:01,038 --> 00:59:04,291
I'm pleased to tell you that I've
screened both your sets of genes...

587
00:59:04,416 --> 00:59:06,376
and there are no Code 46 issues.

588
00:59:06,501 --> 00:59:10,338
It is perfectly safe for you to marry.
In fact, I'd recommend it.

589
00:59:10,797 --> 00:59:13,467
You both have the code
for high intelligence.

590
00:59:14,718 --> 00:59:17,012
- Thank you.
- Thank you very much.

591
00:59:19,347 --> 00:59:20,891
Do you know this woman?

592
00:59:21,975 --> 00:59:24,102
I'm looking for her.

593
00:59:24,311 --> 00:59:27,522
You must have found her, hombre,
if you have her hair.

594
00:59:27,606 --> 00:59:30,275
It was given to me by relatives.

595
00:59:32,444 --> 00:59:36,072
- What's your relationship to this woman?
- I just want to know about her.

596
00:59:37,282 --> 00:59:39,242
You can't liaise with her.

597
00:59:39,785 --> 00:59:42,537
See this? This is your DNA.

598
00:59:43,497 --> 00:59:45,582
A 50% match with the hair samples.

599
00:59:46,166 --> 00:59:47,501
And here...

600
00:59:48,919 --> 00:59:50,504
is the DNA of your mother.

601
00:59:50,629 --> 00:59:53,840
A 100% match. Genetically identical.

602
00:59:54,341 --> 00:59:58,053
Any liaison with this woman
would be a Code 46 violation.

603
00:59:59,846 --> 01:00:02,724
- How can that be?
- Anything's possible in vitro.

604
01:00:03,308 --> 01:00:06,520
Your mother was one of a batch
of 24 cloned fetuses.

605
01:00:06,812 --> 01:00:09,815
This hair is from your mother
or one of her genetic twins.

606
01:00:10,398 --> 01:00:14,528
- This woman is identical to my mother?
- No.

607
01:00:17,614 --> 01:00:18,573
Diet...

608
01:00:18,907 --> 01:00:22,410
climate, environment, accident...

609
01:00:22,577 --> 01:00:25,247
surgery, the stars, God.

610
01:00:26,039 --> 01:00:28,208
We aren't prisoners of our genes.

611
01:00:29,835 --> 01:00:32,045
Is this hair from your mother?

612
01:00:33,088 --> 01:00:34,089
No.

613
01:00:35,841 --> 01:00:39,136
- Are you in love with this woman?
- Why?

614
01:00:40,679 --> 01:00:42,681
- Is she pregnant?
- No.

615
01:00:43,974 --> 01:00:47,435
- Were you naturally conceived?
- In vitro.

616
01:00:48,478 --> 01:00:51,648
Your nurture parents will have
your records, if that's any help.

617
01:00:51,731 --> 01:00:53,191
They're dead.

618
01:00:54,067 --> 01:00:55,360
I'm sorry.

619
01:01:26,057 --> 01:01:28,143
<i>If we're frightened, we run.</i>

620
01:01:28,393 --> 01:01:30,020
<i>It's our instinct.</i>

621
01:01:30,395 --> 01:01:34,232
<i>Adrenalin pumps round the body,
the muscles contract...</i>

622
01:01:34,316 --> 01:01:37,402
<i>our heart beats faster, and we run.</i>

623
01:01:38,945 --> 01:01:40,655
<i>We run for our lives.</i>

624
01:01:40,739 --> 01:01:42,324
<i>We run for safety...</i>

625
01:01:42,449 --> 01:01:46,119
<i>for our home, our families, our loved ones.</i>

626
01:01:49,122 --> 01:01:50,582
Sylvie.

627
01:01:50,665 --> 01:01:53,501
<i>You're driving.
I don't want you to drive and call.</i>

628
01:01:53,752 --> 01:01:56,254
I'm on my way to the airport.
I'll be home tomorrow.

629
01:01:56,379 --> 01:01:58,673
<i>- Catch the bad guy?
- Every time.</i>

630
01:01:59,758 --> 01:02:02,177
<i>William, I love you.</i>

631
01:02:03,136 --> 01:02:05,221
<i>I love you, too.</i>

632
01:02:05,347 --> 01:02:07,766
<i>Daddy? Hello. How are you?</i>

633
01:02:09,768 --> 01:02:11,728
<i>- Love you.
- Me you.</i>

634
01:02:12,312 --> 01:02:14,773
<i>See you later.</i>

635
01:02:38,505 --> 01:02:40,799
Hi. I need a ticket to Seattle.

636
01:02:41,883 --> 01:02:44,803
It's completely red, sir. It's out of date.

637
01:02:45,345 --> 01:02:47,472
See? You're not covered for the Asea area.

638
01:02:47,931 --> 01:02:50,976
But I don't wanna be here.
I wanna leave, I wanna go home.

639
01:02:51,101 --> 01:02:53,728
- I'm covered for home, right?
- I really don't know, sir.

640
01:02:53,812 --> 01:02:55,105
I am covered for home.

641
01:02:55,188 --> 01:02:59,275
But you're not at home, sir.
You're aqui in Shanghai without cover.

642
01:02:59,526 --> 01:03:03,279
I got an idea. Why don't we just kick me out
in the general direction of home?

643
01:03:03,530 --> 01:03:07,409
You can't fly uncovered, sir.
You can't be in the Asea area without cover.

644
01:03:07,534 --> 01:03:10,620
What am I gonna do,
piss out the window at 60,000 feet?

645
01:03:10,704 --> 01:03:14,165
I really wouldn't know enough
about your character to say, sir.

646
01:03:15,083 --> 01:03:18,169
Maybe I can guess something
about your character.

647
01:03:18,670 --> 01:03:20,297
These are particularly fun.

648
01:03:20,755 --> 01:03:22,674
I'm afraid you guessed wrong, sir.

649
01:03:22,757 --> 01:03:26,219
I'm a Christian scientist.
I don't believe in drugs or coffee.

650
01:03:26,678 --> 01:03:27,804
Damn.

651
01:03:28,722 --> 01:03:30,265
I'm all out of Bibles.

652
01:04:05,258 --> 01:04:06,551
<i>Can I come in?</i>

653
01:04:06,676 --> 01:04:07,886
Can I stop you?

654
01:04:17,771 --> 01:04:19,105
I need your help.

655
01:04:19,606 --> 01:04:21,024
Where have you been?

656
01:04:21,733 --> 01:04:23,777
Lo siento. I had something to do.

657
01:04:25,904 --> 01:04:29,741
I shouldn't be in Shanghai.
I should be in Seattle.

658
01:04:30,116 --> 01:04:32,077
You knew that last night.

659
01:04:32,452 --> 01:04:34,704
- I have to go.
- So go.

660
01:04:35,789 --> 01:04:37,040
I can't.

661
01:04:37,749 --> 01:04:41,419
My papel was red. I can't get out.

662
01:04:47,342 --> 01:04:49,094
You tried already?

663
01:04:49,427 --> 01:04:51,388
You were just going to disappear.

664
01:04:57,936 --> 01:04:59,312
You say that too much.

665
01:04:59,813 --> 01:05:02,315
I need to go home.

666
01:05:07,737 --> 01:05:09,697
<i>- You've got a family.
- Si.</i>

667
01:05:11,491 --> 01:05:13,910
<i>- Chico or chica?
- Chico.</i>

668
01:05:18,790 --> 01:05:22,252
He must think you're a real hero
for catching bad guys like me.

669
01:05:23,586 --> 01:05:25,046
Something like that.

670
01:05:29,384 --> 01:05:32,303
Well, you know what they say:
"The Sphinx knows best."

671
01:05:35,306 --> 01:05:37,934
Maybe there's a reason you can't go home.

672
01:05:42,480 --> 01:05:44,149
It's a fake, okay?

673
01:05:44,691 --> 01:05:47,110
I have to swap it for a genuine papel.

674
01:05:53,241 --> 01:05:55,577
I'll meet you at the airport at 7:00, okay?

675
01:05:59,080 --> 01:06:00,206
Come on.

676
01:06:17,223 --> 01:06:20,768
My name is Maria Gonzalez
and I have an access problem.

677
01:06:20,852 --> 01:06:23,688
I have a new finger
and it needs to be recoded.

678
01:06:23,771 --> 01:06:26,399
<i>- Just hold on a moment, please?
- Gracias.</i>

679
01:06:30,528 --> 01:06:33,573
<i>- Buenos dias.
- Bueno. So good to see you.</i>

680
01:06:33,865 --> 01:06:35,241
I have an access problem.

681
01:06:35,366 --> 01:06:38,203
I have a new finger
and I need it to be recoded.

682
01:06:38,286 --> 01:06:40,830
I know. You've been relocated.

683
01:06:41,915 --> 01:06:43,833
- Sorry?
- You have been relocated.

684
01:06:43,917 --> 01:06:45,502
You will work here now.

685
01:06:46,211 --> 01:06:48,213
Why don't you come inside?

686
01:06:54,469 --> 01:06:57,388
<i>- William, where are you?
- Still in Shanghai.</i>

687
01:06:57,889 --> 01:06:59,224
<i>Isn't your cover out?</i>

688
01:06:59,432 --> 01:07:01,726
<i>- I've extended it.
- No, you haven't.</i>

689
01:07:02,268 --> 01:07:05,230
<i>- Where is Maria Gonzalez?
- No lo se.</i>

690
01:07:05,313 --> 01:07:09,067
<i>Why did you remove her from Mai Lin Clinic
without authorization?</i>

691
01:07:09,150 --> 01:07:11,194
<i>- She was a suspect.
- Was?</i>

692
01:07:13,029 --> 01:07:14,030
Is.

693
01:07:14,614 --> 01:07:16,574
<i>You seem upset, William.</i>

694
01:07:17,075 --> 01:07:19,619
<i>Report to the Shanghai office, today.</i>

695
01:07:20,161 --> 01:07:22,080
<i>They will take over the case.</i>

696
01:07:54,779 --> 01:07:57,824
Get me whatever you can,
but get it today, yeah?

697
01:10:18,631 --> 01:10:22,218
It's a single exit cover. Valid for today only.

698
01:10:23,511 --> 01:10:25,346
Seattle flights leave from Zone C.

699
01:10:28,891 --> 01:10:30,560
I do remember you.

700
01:10:31,853 --> 01:10:33,354
From a dream.

701
01:10:35,314 --> 01:10:37,024
From my birthday dream.

702
01:10:46,325 --> 01:10:47,827
You should go home.

703
01:10:55,042 --> 01:10:56,043
No.

704
01:11:10,725 --> 01:11:12,268
Two for Jebel Ali.

705
01:11:12,393 --> 01:11:14,395
- Which flight, sir?
- Next flight.

706
01:11:14,854 --> 01:11:16,230
Do you have cover?

707
01:11:16,355 --> 01:11:17,732
I'm resident here.

708
01:11:18,775 --> 01:11:21,235
Sorry, I forgot. It's my new finger.

709
01:11:23,446 --> 01:11:26,491
Okay. Thanks for choosing
Pan Worldwide Airways.

710
01:11:26,574 --> 01:11:28,326
Have a safe journey.

711
01:11:32,455 --> 01:11:37,126
<i>I'd always dreamt of Jebel Ali.
The Jebel Ali of my father's stories.</i>

712
01:11:37,710 --> 01:11:42,089
<i>He told me you could do anything there,
as long as you wanted it enough.</i>

713
01:12:07,949 --> 01:12:09,450
You know what?

714
01:12:10,284 --> 01:12:15,039
Every time I ever imagined this,
I always imagined being with you.

715
01:12:15,831 --> 01:12:17,542
Even though we'd never met.

716
01:12:30,972 --> 01:12:32,557
- You okay?
- Yeah.

717
01:12:49,282 --> 01:12:51,659
We're looking for a place to stay.

718
01:12:52,201 --> 01:12:54,203
Come, we are going, come.

719
01:13:01,669 --> 01:13:03,421
You've never been al fuera.

720
01:13:04,046 --> 01:13:07,633
<i>So I could be your guide, your teacher.</i>

721
01:13:08,092 --> 01:13:09,927
Three pakoras.

722
01:13:26,527 --> 01:13:29,071
We're looking for a room. We have cover.

723
01:13:29,363 --> 01:13:33,200
No one has cover for over here.
You can't buy cover for here.

724
01:13:33,618 --> 01:13:36,537
- Residents sleep at their own risk.
- But we can have a room?

725
01:13:37,038 --> 01:13:39,749
A room, food, a game of chess.

726
01:13:40,207 --> 01:13:43,920
There's a shower through there.
You're covered in dust.

727
01:13:54,930 --> 01:13:57,183
It will be noisy, lo siento.

728
01:13:58,392 --> 01:14:00,144
That doesn't matter.

729
01:14:01,312 --> 01:14:03,856
We'll sleep through anything.
We're so tired.

730
01:14:03,981 --> 01:14:06,484
- Have you come a long way?
- Yes.

731
01:14:08,986 --> 01:14:10,404
My wife made that.

732
01:14:11,447 --> 01:14:13,240
Before she passed on.

733
01:14:13,324 --> 01:14:15,952
Maybe think about her un poco
before you sleep.

734
01:14:19,246 --> 01:14:20,665
Pleasure to have you.

735
01:14:27,672 --> 01:14:29,090
Will you put this on?

736
01:14:53,239 --> 01:14:55,700
- Does your wife look like you?
- No.

737
01:14:58,452 --> 01:15:00,037
How did you meet?

738
01:15:01,497 --> 01:15:04,000
We worked together until we had Jim.

739
01:15:05,960 --> 01:15:07,628
You must miss him.

740
01:15:08,295 --> 01:15:09,338
Yes.

741
01:15:11,048 --> 01:15:12,383
Sing.

742
01:15:13,259 --> 01:15:14,343
What?

743
01:15:15,636 --> 01:15:17,096
I want to hear you sing.

744
01:15:18,139 --> 01:15:19,598
I can't sing.

745
01:15:30,443 --> 01:15:31,736
I'm sorry.

746
01:15:33,487 --> 01:15:36,490
It's okay. It's not your fault.

747
01:15:45,916 --> 01:15:47,251
It's viral.

748
01:15:50,921 --> 01:15:52,381
The Sphinx...

749
01:15:54,175 --> 01:15:56,010
gave you a virus.

750
01:15:58,304 --> 01:16:01,724
What, like an anti-William virus?

751
01:16:03,184 --> 01:16:05,895
It's involuntary. It's like adrenaline.

752
01:16:08,022 --> 01:16:09,523
When you're...

753
01:16:09,940 --> 01:16:13,360
scared of something,
your body gets ready to run away.

754
01:16:16,030 --> 01:16:17,823
I'm not scared of you.

755
01:16:17,907 --> 01:16:20,743
I know. But your body is.

756
01:16:29,251 --> 01:16:31,545
I want you to make love to me.

757
01:16:37,968 --> 01:16:39,970
Make me make love to you.

758
01:18:07,433 --> 01:18:08,809
I love you.

759
01:19:59,086 --> 01:20:01,922
<i>You must have known
the way the virus works.</i>

760
01:20:03,257 --> 01:20:05,718
<i>Was there nothing you could do to stop me?</i>

761
01:20:09,680 --> 01:20:10,931
I need to make a call.

762
01:20:11,015 --> 01:20:13,142
- All calls are logged.
- That's okay.

763
01:20:13,726 --> 01:20:16,145
<i>- Phone is la-bas.
- Gracias.</i>

764
01:20:22,318 --> 01:20:26,322
My name is Maria Gonzalez,
and I'm reporting a Code 46 violation.

765
01:20:26,697 --> 01:20:29,366
Gracias. What is your location?

766
01:20:29,950 --> 01:20:33,245
- What is this address?
- 168 Shada Perrera.

767
01:20:37,207 --> 01:20:39,668
<i>- Please wait there.
- I'll be right here.</i>

768
01:21:08,280 --> 01:21:09,490
Wake up.

769
01:21:12,493 --> 01:21:13,702
Come on.

770
01:21:19,166 --> 01:21:22,836
- We have to go.
- No, I want to stay here forever.

771
01:21:34,681 --> 01:21:36,642
See? I can kiss you now.

772
01:21:37,976 --> 01:21:39,853
We have to go. Come on.

773
01:21:41,021 --> 01:21:43,524
- Something's happened.
- Okay.

774
01:21:44,525 --> 01:21:46,151
We need a car. Can you help?

775
01:21:46,527 --> 01:21:49,446
Cars are expensive here.
Even more than in the city.

776
01:21:50,155 --> 01:21:51,949
I've got these.

777
01:21:56,703 --> 01:21:59,623
I need money. People have to eat.

778
01:22:05,337 --> 01:22:06,880
That's all I've got.

779
01:22:08,841 --> 01:22:10,008
Not enough.

780
01:22:16,223 --> 01:22:20,894
Hey, Sono, take them to the sierat shop.
Tell Farrukh to give them a Padmini.

781
01:22:38,412 --> 01:22:40,164
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

782
01:23:37,221 --> 01:23:38,514
<i>I love you.</i>

783
01:23:52,110 --> 01:23:55,531
Okay, all right.
That's enough playing now. Stop.

784
01:25:04,725 --> 01:25:06,810
<i>You went before a tribunal.</i>

785
01:25:07,269 --> 01:25:10,689
<i>They decided the empathy virus
had affected your judgment.</i>

786
01:25:10,772 --> 01:25:12,941
<i>So they took away your memory of me.</i>

787
01:25:13,567 --> 01:25:15,736
<i>Just like they had wiped
